The paper deals with visual attention tracking, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of shared attention modeling and attentional push also suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. Finally, the incorporation of attention modeling algorithms to improve prediction accuracy could also relate to machine learning (cs.LG).
